SUMMARY:Phantoms of the Past
DESCRIPTION:Delhi is deeply haunted. What it is haunted by\, is a different question altogether.  \nIn the shadow of medieval mosques and Mughal tombs\, the past refuses to stay buried. Saints\, Sultans\, poets\, and lovers—all linger in the city’s imagination\, their stories shaping how we remember what once was. Ghosted is Eric Chopra’s account of why folklore clusters around ruins\, why humans are drawn to places with reputations for the uncanny\, and why history\, everywhere in the world\, is so haunted.  \nThe evening begins with a dramatic reading from Ghosted\, followed by a conversation between Eric Chopra and Vikramajit Ram\, with visuals of the monuments. The session then opens to an audience Q&A. \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/phantoms-of-the-past/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Culture,Heritage,History
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thumbnail-2-e1777978632518.jpg
