UID:89362-1779040800-1779046200@bangaloreinternationalcentre.org
SUMMARY:From Crime to Cosmos
DESCRIPTION:Language: English  \nCan humans give away their gods in marriage? Can a crime investigation reveal the limits of human knowledge? \nWriting in Tamil\, Jeyamohan’s stories swing between the past and present\, where everyone’s destiny is entangled with forces beyond their comprehension. Two of his books were recently published in English: One Million Footsteps\, translated by Iswarya V\, investigates what drives humans irresistibly towards transgression; The Daughter of Kumari\, translated by Suchitra Ramachandran\, reveals the personal\, historical and mythical bonds between humans and their gods. \nBut fiction is only as impactful as the truth it carries. And not every truth can survive the journey across languages. \nIn this session\, author and translators sit together to discuss where these stories come from and what it takes to carry them across culture and context. They will take audience questions after the discussion. Jeyamohan will then be signing books. \nPresented by: \nVishnupuram Literary Circle\, Bengaluru \n
URL:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/event/from-crime-to-cosmos/
LOCATION:Bangalore International Centre\, 7\, 4th Main Road\, Domlur II Stage\, Bangalore\, Karnataka\, 560071\, India
CATEGORIES:Books,Fiction,Literature
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://bangaloreinternationalcentre.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/05/Thumbnail-4.jpg
END:VEVENT
